              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "ZCA4t",
                  "name": "DropCapPara",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "gap": 16,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "DJRaL",
                      "name": "dropCap",
                      "fill": "#9B1B30",
                      "effect": {
                        "type": "shadow",
                        "shadowType": "outer",
                        "color": "#9B1B3030",
                        "blur": 20
                      },
                      "content": "T",
                      "lineHeight": 0.8,
                      "fontFamily": "Cormorant Garamond",
                      "fontSize": 72,
                      "fontWeight": "600"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "jM7X7",
                      "name": "dropText",
                      "fill": "#C8C8C8",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "he ballroom emptied slowly, like blood draining from a wound. Elena stood at the edge of the marble floor, her crimson dress pooling around her feet like spilled wine. She could feel his gaze before she saw him — a heat that pressed against her skin, demanding acknowledgment.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.85,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 17,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "5oniD",
                  "name": "para2",
                  "fill": "#C8C8C8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "\"You came.\" Damien's voice was low, a rumble that vibrated through the empty hall. He emerged from the shadows near the grand staircase, his dark suit absorbing what little light remained. His jaw was set, but his eyes — those treacherous eyes — betrayed something she'd never seen in them before. Vulnerability.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.85,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "NbclY",
                  "name": "para3",
                  "fill": "#C8C8C8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "\"I shouldn't have,\" she whispered, but her feet carried her forward anyway, closing the distance between them like gravity was a force that only existed between their bodies. The chandelier above cast fractured light across his face, turning him into something half-divine, half-dangerous.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.85,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "EmXx3",
                  "name": "para4",
                  "fill": "#C8C8C8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "He reached for her hand. His fingers were cold — they always were — but where they touched her wrist, fire bloomed beneath her skin. \"There's something I need to tell you,\" he said, and for the first time, the man who commanded empires sounded afraid. \"About the night your father disappeared.\"",
                  "lineHeight": 1.85,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
